{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"acaa05e7-3270-4281-86a5-aeb1bbf6924e","content":"Neither — use **`dotnet watch`** to benefit from hot reload.\n\n- `dotnet watch test` — re-runs tests automatically when files change.\n- `dotnet watch run` — restarts/hot-reloads an app on changes.\n\n`dotnet test` and `dotnet run` execute once and exit; they don't watch for file changes. The `watch` command is what provides the hot reload behavior.\n\nFor your test project, you'd use:\n\n```bash\ndotnet watch test\n```","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"a5b1b355-593b-4905-8634-b54cfcff1a06","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about .NET hot reload and whether to use `dotnet test` or `dotnet run`. Let me look at the project files to understand the context.","outputTokens":169,"requestId":"3021:3CD672:448ABB1:4B5E22F:6A031068"},"id":"a811c6ad-04fb-4597-959b-44750707af0c","timestamp":"2026-05-12T11:35:13.348Z","parentId":"96b5a4fc-6ad9-44b9-aaeb-36309b15fc84"}
